         <div class="comment_content"> 
          <p>The Fake Scandal Committee apparently ran out of ideas for new fake scandals so are now retreading old fake scandals. And in case anyone is not up to speed here: a bunch of right wing/Tea Party political groups tried to lie their way into getting a tax exempt status not meant for political groups; they then complained to their Republican reps when their applications were held up by an understaffed IRS department dealing with vague law and poor direction on the matter (as well as poorly filled out applications); the Congressional Republicans saw this as another fake scandal opportunity, so they cranked up their Fake Outrage machine to make it into a Big Effin’ Deal; the mainstream press in turn cranked up their Botch-O-Matic Reportathon machine; and at the end none of the right wing/Tea Party groups had their applications denied and everyone lived angrily and fingerpointedly ever after. The end (well….)</p> 
